name: Translinguistic Volume Three
description:
Focusing on Philadelphia, New York, Northern California Graffiti. As always TRANSLINGUISTIC is a Black and White zine hand arranged in a collage style. Highly aesthetic layouts and Graffiti of course. It is pretty strictly handstyles, bombs, pieces, and feights.  Lots of mined fortune cookie wisdom as always is included. 40 Pages 

Comes with lots of Stickers and things

name: TRANSLINGUISTIC VOLUME 2
description: Volume two features hand cut and pasted collage-style photo documentation of California and Oregon graffiti art, as well as art made by graffiti writers. Place featured in this issue include; Portland, San Francisco, Oakland, Santa Cruz, Southern California. Streets, Cuts, Trains, Trucks, Tracks and more! 70 pages Printed on high quality black and white (Xeroxed) EACH ORDER COMES WITH STICKERS AND DRAWINGS **SECOND EDITION NOW AVAILABLE**

name: TRANSLINGUISTIC VOLUME 1
description:
THIS IS THE THIRD AND LAST RE-PRINT OF TRANSLINGUISTIC VOL. 1

Get it b4 it's gone!

~ Showcasing Northern California graffiti and art produced/ documented between 2008 and now. This issue is featuring the work of; Translinguistic, Santacruzandsuch, Alex, Clausen, and others. 68 Pages, high gloss black and white printing. Each order comes with a hand selected sticker/goodie assortment.
